SIMPLE: wrapper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrapper
<hw>Wrap"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, wraps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That in which anything is wrapped, or inclosed;
envelope; covering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, a loose outer garment; an article of
dress intended to be wrapped round the person; <as>as, a morning
<ex>wrapper</ex>; a gentleman's <ex>wrapper</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wraprascal</ent>⟦br⟧
